The paper discusses a deep learning strategy for improving model generalisation performance, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The approach is evaluated on both coarse-grained object categorisation tasks and fine-grained person instance identification tasks, indicating that it could potentially fall under multiple sub-categories. However, given the focus on deep learning and model optimisation, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely given the evaluation on image datasets. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories given the focus on deep learning and neural networks. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible given the potential application of the approach to natural language processing tasks.
